<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-05T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-05T04:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/587:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-05T10:00:00+01:00">December 5, 1929—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:09 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>40. Department’s circular telegram December 1 [, 4 p.m.]. Foreign
                            Minister has given me oral assurance that Albania will immediately
                                comply.<note n="68" xml:id="d329fn68">See telegram No. 99, December
                                14, from the Ambassador in Italy, <ref target="#pg_421">p.
                                421</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>